  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA29">
<l>pēyccipā luṇṭa perumāṉaip pērnteṭut</l>
<l>tāycci mulaikoṭuttā ḷañcātē – vāytta</l>
<l>viruḷār tirumēṉi yiṉpavaḷac cevvāy</l>
<l>teruḷā moḻiyāṉaic cērntu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Again taking up the great lord who had drunk the milk of the demoness</l>
<l>the cowherdess fearlessly gave [him her] breast,</l>
<l>joining with the one with words that were babbled<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">The phrase teruḷā moḻi, induced by etukai, takes up the frequent motif of the little child’s speech that is not yet clear in pronounciation, that is, baby talk.</note>, a sweet coral-red mouth</l>
<l>[and] a shining body full of lush darkness.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
